<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1265,1430,1457]" box="[151,1265,1430,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,1265,1430,1457]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1265,1430,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
Key to males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Santos" authorityYear="1965" box="[352,482,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Minagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,482,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Minagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cercus in mediodorsal view, except when otherwise indicated)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="179" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1499,1991]" box="[151,1436,1499,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1499,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
1. Larger species (
<quantity box="[378,483,1499,1521]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="6.1" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" unit="mm" value="57.5" valueMax="61.0" valueMin="54.0">54−61 mm</quantity>
total length), abdomen 2x longer than Fw length (
<figureCitation box="[967,1036,1499,1521]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1433,1458]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,532,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,525,1408]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: (a) caldense, São Roque de Minas, at ECOEVO; (b) caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (d) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875353" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875353/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
)................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos" authorityYear="1965" box="[1252,1436,1500,1521]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Telagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mecistogastrum">
<emphasis box="[1252,1436,1500,1521]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">M. mecistogastrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1499,1991]" box="[151,1436,1529,1551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1529,1551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
1’. Medium species (
<quantity box="[395,501,1529,1550]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" unit="mm" value="37.5" valueMax="44.0" valueMin="31.0">31−44 mm</quantity>
total length), abdomen less than 2x the length of Fw (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1072,1163,1529,1551]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1433,1458]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,532,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,525,1408]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: (a) caldense, São Roque de Minas, at ECOEVO; (b) caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (d) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875353" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875353/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 1b, e</figureCitation>
)..................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1499,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
2. Dorsal plate of cercus broad; ventrobasal portion only 1/5 of the cercus length (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1072,1558,1580]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
u−x, 8g−h); tubercle digit-like with a rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[369,439,1587,1609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1265,1290]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,187,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,181,1239]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. S1 tubercle; (a) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (b) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (c) ♀ caldense ALLOTYPE, Poços de Caldas, at MNRJ; (d) ♀ caldense, SCNP, at ECOEVO; (e) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (f) ♀ canaanense ALLOTYPE, Santa Tereza, at MNRJ; (g) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (h) ♀ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (i) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (j) ♀ ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (k) ♂ waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM; (l) ♀ waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875355" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875355/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 2k</figureCitation>
)......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1436,1587,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Minagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waltheri">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,1587,1609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">M. waltheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1499,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
2’. Dorsal plate of cercus narrow (as in 
<figureCitation box="[579,669,1617,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 3h, t</figureCitation>
); ventrobasal portion at least 1/2 of cercus length (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1214,1279,1617,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1259,1279,1617,1639]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" unit="t" value="3.0">3t</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); tubercle never digit-like or with rounded apex.......................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1499,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
3. Longitudinal ridge of cercus not entire (i.e. disrupted along its length) forming a basal and an apical ridge, more pronounced on the distal 1/2 (
<figureCitation box="[391,457,1705,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 3l</figureCitation>
); sclerotized apex of cercus globose with no apparent teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1108,1705,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Figs. 3l</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1118,1144,1705,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1439,1464]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,188,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,181,1414]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male anal appendages of Minagrion holotypes probably lost during the fire at MNRJ in 2018; (a–b) caldense, Poços de Caldas; (c–d) canaanense, Santa Tereza; (e–f) ribeiroi (Telagrion ribeiroi), Recreio dos Bandeirantes; (g–h) waltheri (Telagrion serracipoense), Jaboticatubas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875367/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">8d</figureCitation>
); tubercle quadrangular with a slightly concave apex (
<figureCitation box="[447,515,1734,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1265,1290]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,187,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,181,1239]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. S1 tubercle; (a) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (b) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (c) ♀ caldense ALLOTYPE, Poços de Caldas, at MNRJ; (d) ♀ caldense, SCNP, at ECOEVO; (e) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (f) ♀ canaanense ALLOTYPE, Santa Tereza, at MNRJ; (g) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (h) ♀ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (i) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (j) ♀ ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (k) ♂ waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM; (l) ♀ waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875355" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875355/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 2e</figureCitation>
)................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Santos" authorityYear="1967" box="[1291,1436,1735,1756]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Minagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canaanense">
<emphasis box="[1291,1436,1735,1756]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">M. canaanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1499,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
3’. Longitudinal ridge of cercus entire (i.e., a continuous ridge along its length, as in 
<figureCitation box="[1032,1124,1763,1785]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 3d, t</figureCitation>
); sclerotized apex of cercus not globose, with evident teeth; tubercle not as above............................................................ 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1499,1991]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
4. Cercus shorter than S 
<quantity box="[431,481,1822,1844]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
lateral view, (
<figureCitation box="[617,682,1822,1844]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
q–t, 8e–f) and with acute sclerotized apex, with one strong tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1388,1822,1844]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
Figs. 
<quantity box="[1368,1388,1822,1843]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" unit="t" value="3.0">3t</quantity>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1399,1424,1822,1844]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1439,1464]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,188,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,181,1414]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male anal appendages of Minagrion holotypes probably lost during the fire at MNRJ in 2018; (a–b) caldense, Poços de Caldas; (c–d) canaanense, Santa Tereza; (e–f) ribeiroi (Telagrion ribeiroi), Recreio dos Bandeirantes; (g–h) waltheri (Telagrion serracipoense), Jaboticatubas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875367/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">8e</figureCitation>
